亂噏，快手叫班支那廢老托市啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7fdb740c4cbf5d035bc7def08a297013be597c31","tid":1831563,"uid":55905,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-20T22:35:32.000Z","msg":"年頭燈到以家，咁多單野個市都沒跌，仲準備上三萬<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"81eaab5f94fdf9d86423b18d4dc90ac6d4a81343","tid":1831563,"uid":86756,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T00:45:24.000Z","msg":"面仔隻7500咩價入"},{"pid":"9f0f85495ede91b5606c0525b3e79b0a8f3a095c","tid":1831563,"uid":33263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T00:54:45.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/hongkong-protests-moodys-idUSL3N2672AH\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fhongkong-protests-moodys-idUSL3N2672AH&d=%2F7nbYOXxgzDTTn%2FAx8VV960IH4hhGWFtD%2BQErH2Rjq0%3D&h=c4b51f7d\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fhongkong-protests-moodys-idUSL3N2672AH&h=434e1fee\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/hongkong-protests-moodys-idUSL3N2672AH</a><br />\n<br />\nMoody&rsquo;s downgraded Hong Kong&rsquo;s credit rating one notch to &ldquo;Aa3&rdquo; from &ldquo;Aa2&rdquo; on Monday, saying its view on the strength in the Chinese-ruled city&rsquo;s institutions and governance is &ldquo;lower than previously estimated.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nAnti-government protesters attend a rally to call for democratic reforms in Hong Kong, China January 19, 2020. REUTERS/Tyrone Siu<br />\nThe agency, however, moved its outlook to stable from negative.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The absence of tangible plans to address either the political or economic and social concerns of the Hong Kong population that have come to the fore in the past nine months may reflect weaker inherent institutional capacity than Moody&rsquo;s had previously assessed,&rdquo; the agency said in a statement.<br />\n<br />\nThe agency also said that there has been a lack of clarity from Hong Kong&rsquo;s government on its response to the direct council elections late last year that saw pro-democracy candidates win by record numbers.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;<ins><span style=\"color: orange;\">Pressures on Hong Kong&rsquo;s institutions undermine its credit profile directly,&rdquo; </span></ins>Moody&rsquo;s added.<br />\n<br />\nIn a statement on Tuesday, Hong Kong&rsquo;s government said it strongly disagreed with Moody&rsquo;s assessment and was &ldquo;deeply disappointed&rdquo; by the decision.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Although Hong Kong has faced the most severe social unrest since its return to the Motherland in the past seven months or so, the HKSAR Government, with the staunch support of the Central Government, has firmly upheld the &lsquo;one country, two systems&rsquo; principle and handled the situation in accordance with the law to curb violence on its own to restore social order as soon as possible,&rdquo; it said.<br />\n<br />\nMoody&rsquo;s said its stable outlook reflects Hong Kong&rsquo;s superior fiscal strength and consistent macroeconomic stability."},{"pid":"7dbda543561b1fb260e3a06aca0172c41b441166","tid":1831563,"uid":33263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T00:55:13.000Z","msg":"The agency&rsquo;s move comes as many Hong Kongers continue to take to the streets, with thousands gathering in a central park on Sunday calling for democratic reforms leading to clashes with the police.<br />\n<br />\nProtests escalated in June over a since-withdrawn bill which would have allowed extraditions to mainland China, where courts are controlled by the Communist Party. They have since broadened to several demands, including universal suffrage.<br />\n<br />\nMoody&rsquo;s called the response by Hong Kong&rsquo;s government to political demands by parts of the population and concerns about living standards, housing costs and equality of economic opportunities to be &ldquo;notably slow, tentative and inconclusive.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nThe government said it was &ldquo;proactively&rdquo; engaging various groups of people through dialogue.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The persistent social unrest reflects that there are deep-seated problems in society in Hong Kong, on which the Government will conduct an independent review soon,&rdquo; the government statement said.<br />\n<br />\nIn September, Fitch downgraded Hong Kong&rsquo;s rating to &ldquo;AA&rdquo; from &ldquo;AA+&rdquo;."},{"pid":"2ccb0123746f361f9a0bc955553dbe912aa393c6","tid":1831563,"uid":33263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"7dbda543561b1fb260e3a06aca0172c41b441166","tid":1831563,"uid":33263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T00:55:13.000Z","msg":"The agency&rsquo;s move comes as many Hong Kongers continue to take to the streets, with thousands gathering in a central park on Sunday calling for democratic reforms leading to clashes with the police.<br />\n<br />\nProtests escalated in June over a since-withdrawn bill which would have allowed extraditions to mainland China, where courts are controlled by the Communist Party. They have since broadened to several demands, including universal suffrage.<br />\n<br />\nMoody&rsquo;s called the response by Hong Kong&rsquo;s government to political demands by parts of the population and concerns about living standards, housing costs and equality of economic opportunities to be &ldquo;notably slow, tentative and inconclusive.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nThe government said it was &ldquo;proactively&rdquo; engaging various groups of people through dialogue.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The persistent social unrest reflects that there are deep-seated problems in society in Hong Kong, on which the Government will conduct an independent review soon,&rdquo; the government statement said.<br />\n<br />\nIn September, Fitch downgraded Hong Kong&rsquo;s rating to &ldquo;AA&rdquo; from &ldquo;AA+&rdquo;."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T01:58:36.000Z","msg":"跌左500點<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ae0b6a07e430bdac8efb39fdd32301e9ea4c2ec0","tid":1831563,"uid":47080,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T02:03:30.000Z","msg":"破燈<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/yipes.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f1c55fc1a161f82857365f59ef811a22010fb5eb","tid":1831563,"uid":28279,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T02:06:00.000Z","msg":"好燈<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/369.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e0909fcf2ae117f47d457c40e4f75d714fca30d2","tid":1831563,"uid":28853,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T02:14:49.000Z","msg":"要俾貴息借錢<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4b1141c443408099cb2b354558ac4a2ff4c8dc03","tid":1831563,"uid":270156,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f1422c442d48fde069abbe84a43f6217c59d46fe","tid":1831563,"uid":172668,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-01-20T14:20:03.000Z","msg":"聽日政策市<br />\n一定大升"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T02:16:25.000Z","msg":"升你入棺材"},{"pid":"6ae67e17473073ff7d49e343c72a275ac5cc163c","tid":1831563,"uid":125888,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f1422c442d48fde069abbe84a43f6217c59d46fe","tid":1831563,"uid":172668,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-01-20T14:20:03.000Z","msg":"聽日政策市<br />\n一定大升"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T02:18:39.000Z","msg":"升災"},{"pid":"7cac03c3e87b2252709152cf84408a854b29abc8","tid":1831563,"uid":172668,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"4b1141c443408099cb2b354558ac4a2ff4c8dc03","tid":1831563,"uid":270156,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f1422c442d48fde069abbe84a43f6217c59d46fe","tid":1831563,"uid":172668,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedB